# gh-agentic-workflow — where rules live

## Primary guidance

- **Agnostic architecture** (slices, hexagonal, monorepo, Makefile invariants): `rules/00-architecture/*.mdc`
- **Standards** (documentation for indexing, pure domain — agnostic): `rules/01-standards/*.mdc`
- **TypeScript / fp-ts domain rules (R1–R4)**: `rules/02-programming-languages/2-*.mdc`
- **NestJS / boundaries (R5–R7) and Vitest**: `rules/03-frameworks-and-libraries/3-*.mdc`
- **Quick overview of Nest + rule index**: [3-nestjs-architecture.mdc](../../rules/03-frameworks-and-libraries/3-nestjs-architecture.mdc)

The duplicate meta file `rules/04-tools-and-configurations/4-specify-rules.mdc` is aligned with this pointer; prefer **one** place for long-form policy: `rules/`.

## SpecKit and plans

Treat `.specify/memory/constitution.md` (if present) and `specs/**/spec.md` as inputs to implementation; they must not contradict the architecture rules in `rules/00-architecture/`.

## Commands

Use the project’s **Makefile** and **package.json** scripts; follow [0-makefile-structure.mdc](../../rules/00-architecture/0-makefile-structure.mdc) and [makefile-conventions skill](../../skills/makefile-conventions/SKILL.md) for make targets.

## AIDD / taxonomy

Rules are filed under `rules/00-…-09-…` with `{N}-{slug}.mdc` names — see [0-rules-structure.mdc](../../rules/00-architecture/0-rules-structure.mdc).

